arcana (0.26.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Snapshot no longer persists code-registered listings (or their
    mailboxes). Root cause of the "zombie listing" bug: a pre-
    consolidation snapshot restored old service addresses that the
    current code doesn't create anymore, leaving mailboxes without
    workers and every send silently timing out.
  * Requires arcana-core 0.12.0 which added `Listing.ephemeral` and
    marks Service.new / Toolset.new registrations with it. The daemon
    now filters ephemeral listings from `Snapshot.save`. Startup order
    stays: (1) code re-registers Toolsets fresh; (2) snapshot restores
    user-registered listings. Ghosts can't reappear.
  * ONE-TIME migration: existing state.json files contain unmarked
    listings (from before the ephemeral flag existed). If you were
    running the daemon on 0.24.0+ with a pre-0.24 snapshot, those
    ghost listings are still in state.json. `sudo rm
    /var/lib/arcana/state.json && sudo systemctl restart arcana`
    clears them once; from then on the fix prevents re-accumulation.
  * Depends on arcana-core ~> 0.12.0.

 -- trans <transfire@gmail.com>  Tue, 15 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0000

arcana (0.25.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * BREAKING: the `capability` field on Directory listings is gone.
    - Server /directory no longer accepts `?capability=` filter.
    - `arcana_register` MCP tool schema drops the `capability` param.
    - `arcana_directory` MCP tool schema drops the `capability` param.
    - Built-in Toolset registrations in bin/arcana.cr drop the
      `capability:` field. Tags are now the discovery surface.
  * Cross-provider discovery uses tags: `arcana_directory tag:"chat"`
    finds every entity that offers a chat tool. Toolsets auto-tag
    their registered tool names on start, so tool names are always
    in the tag list without the user having to double-declare.
  * Redundant tool-name tags trimmed from built-in Toolsets (chat,
    tts, embed, image, markdown, echo appear automatically from
    the tool registrations now).
  * Help topic addressing/discovery text updated.
  * Depends on arcana-core ~> 0.11.0.

 -- trans <transfire@gmail.com>  Tue, 15 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000

arcana (0.24.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * BREAKING: every default provider is now a Toolset. The
    `owner:capability` service addresses are gone from the built-ins.
    - `arcana:echo`, `arcana:markdown` → tools on the `arcana` Toolset
    - `arcana:help` gone (redundant with MCP `initialize` instructions
      and `arcana`'s own directory guide field)
    - `openai:chat`, `openai:embed`, `openai:tts` → tools on the
      `openai` Toolset
    - `anthropic:chat` → tool on the `anthropic` Toolset
    - `gemini:chat` → tool on the `gemini` Toolset
    - `runware:image` → tool on the `runware` Toolset
    - Standalone `arcana` library-as-thing agent listing dropped;
      the `arcana` Toolset is the new listing.
  * Discovery flow becomes uniformly two-step: (1) `arcana_directory`
    to find entities (filter by `tag: "chat"` for chat providers,
    etc.); (2) `{"tool":"help"}` to any entity for its tools manifest.
  * Callers migrating: `deliver to:"openai:chat" payload:{messages:...}`
    becomes `deliver to:"openai" payload:{tool:"chat", messages:...}`.
    Same fields, just prefix with `tool: "<name>"`.
  * `did_you_mean` on old-shape addresses will not cross-suggest
    (the sigil/colon-form split is respected).

