arcana (0.23.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * `@`-sigil convention for agent handles. A project's Claude/Codex
    agent can now register as `@mj` alongside the same project's
    tool service registered as `mj` — two distinct entities on the
    bus, no collision. The sigil is purely a naming convention: the
    bus does not derive kind, ordering, or routing from it. Set
    `kind: "agent"` explicitly on the registration as before.
  * `did_you_mean` is sigil-aware: a typo of `@mj` will not
    cross-suggest `mj` (or vice versa), since they are distinct
    entities by design. Same-group suggestions still work normally.
  * Help topic "addressing" and MCP `arcana_register` tool
    description document the new convention.
  * Depends on arcana-core ~> 0.10.0 (which added `@`-tolerant
    address validation and `Directory.handle?`).

 -- trans <transfire@gmail.com>  Sun, 13 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000

arcana (0.22.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Three scale/robustness wins from the doc/PROTOCOL.md audit.
  * Bounded mailboxes (via arcana-core 0.9.1). Every mailbox
    defaults to `ARCANA_MAILBOX_MAX_QUEUE` (default 10000) messages.
    Deliveries beyond that raise MailboxFull; the sender's send()
    re-raises, /deliver returns an error, event log records
    `message.rejected` with reason `mailbox_full`. Set the env var
    to 0 to disable and go unbounded.
  * Non-blocking prune (via arcana-core 0.9.1). Directory prune no
    longer holds its mutex through both the walk AND the deletes —
    register/lookup can slip through during a large sweep.
  * arcana-mcp keep-alive HTTP. The MCP bridge now uses one
    persistent HTTP::Client instance instead of tearing down and
    rebuilding a TCP connection per REST call. Shaves the TCP
    handshake off every MCP tool call.
  * Depends on arcana-core ~> 0.9.1.

