arcana (0.21.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Identity/capability split. An address is now a routing label, not
    a type marker. Kind (agent/service) and capability (chat/image/tts
    /markdown/...) are separate fields on the listing.
    - POST /register accepts optional `kind` and `capability`.
    - MCP arcana_register gains `kind` and `capability` params.
    - MCP arcana_directory gains a `capability` filter
      (`arcana_directory capability:"chat"` lists all chat services).
    - Built-in services (openai:chat, anthropic:chat, gemini:chat,
      runware:image, openai:tts, openai:embed, arcana:echo,
      arcana:markdown, arcana:help) declare their capability
      explicitly.
    - Help briefing rewritten: addressing is described as free-form
      labels, kind and capability as separate fields.
  * Depends on arcana-core ~> 0.6.0.
  * No wire-format break for existing callers — legacy registrations
    without kind/capability still work via the address-based fallback
    in the Listing constructor (colon = service; capability = right
    half of colon-form).

