arcana (0.19.3-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * /send and /deliver now suggest the closest registered address
    when delivery fails for an unknown one. The 404 response includes
    a structured `did_you_mean: {address, name, description}` field
    and an updated human-readable error string ("...Did you mean 'X'
    (Name)?"). Scoring is substring-containment-first, then
    Levenshtein-normalized; below a similarity threshold the response
    is unchanged. Addresses the recurring case where agents
    re-register under different names and senders retry stale ones.
  * MCP `initialize` instructions briefing now mentions the
    `did_you_mean` field so agents react to it on delivery failure.

